cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY

This paper involves the use of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning algorithms to analyze electronic health records (EHR) related to diabetes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and text analysis. The paper also involves the development and evaluation of deep learning neural network algorithms, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of machine learning classifiers to identify relevant EHR notes also falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with healthcare data, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
